<item>
            <title>[SEC-2773] Non-static declaration of ApplicationListener bean causes premature initialization</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2773</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2574&quot; title=&quot;Default JavaConfig SessionRegistryImpl does not receive SessionDestroyedEvents&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-2574&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-2574&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced an &lt;tt&gt;@Bean&lt;/tt&gt; method declaring a &lt;tt&gt;DelegatingApplicationListener&lt;/tt&gt; on &lt;tt&gt;WebSecurityConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationListeners&lt;/tt&gt; are looked up very early in the container lifecycle and due to the declaring method being an instance method the container needs to initialize the configuration class in its entirety. This in turn causes the container having to lookup the parameters of &lt;tt&gt;setFilterChainProxySecurityConfigurer(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; on a by-type basis which causes initializations of a lot of &lt;tt&gt;Factory&lt;/tt&gt; beans and other configuration classes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Changing the bean declaration to be a &lt;tt&gt;static&lt;/tt&gt; method, prevents the need for the premature instantiation of the configuration class. Pull request coming.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
